#Notes to follow
#ensure that cmd prompt is opened with administrative role
1. From search type 'cmd' and wait for search results to come back
2. Right click on cmd and run as Administrator
3. Paste or Type:
  @"%SystemRoot%\System32\WindowsPowerShell\v1.0\powershell.exe" -NoProfile -InputFormat None -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -Command "iex ((New-Object System.Net.WebClient).DownloadString('https://chocolatey.org/install.ps1'))" && SET "PATH=%PATH%;%ALLUSERSPROFILE%\chocolatey\bin"
4. close cmd prompt and reopen with steps 1 and 2
5. type choco to verify installation
6. Paste or Type:
  choco upgrade chocolatey
7. Paste or Type:
  choco install mysql -y
  # On windows, it may show red text indicating errors...you should be able to ignore.
8. close cmd prompt and reopen with steps 1 and 2
9. type 'mysql -V' to verify mysql installed
10. proceed to file: mysql_login_details
